                        <interp inst="t18510707-name-37" type="given" value="BENJAMIN HERSCHEL"></interp>BENJAMIN HERSCHEL BABBAGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I was on Tower-hill on 1st July, about 4 o'clock in the afternoon. I passed Golding's offices, and just afterwards I missed my handkerchief—I turned, and saw the prisoner within two or three paces of me, looking into the offices—I seized him by both arms, and saw him drop my handkerchief from his right hand—I pushed him into the office—a friend behind me called a policeman, who came and took the prisoner—he said, "Let me go, I am starving"—this is my handkerchief—it has my initials on it.</p>
